Question1: Create a checkbox input feild in HTML
Code: 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>
            anskey1
        </title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>What is your fav food.</h1>
        <label for="mycheckbox"> apple</label>
        <input type="checkbox" id="my checkbox" 
        name="mycheckbox">
        <label for="mycheckbox">Banana</label>
        <input type="checkbox" id="mycheckbox"
        name="mycheckbox">
    </body>
</html>

Question3:How to create a hyperlink that opens in a new tab?
Code:
  Text in a pre element
  	is displayed in a fixed-width
  font, and it preserves
  both      spaces and
  line breaks
Answer:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>
            anskey2
        </title>
    </head>
    <body>
         <a href="#" target="_blank">Click here to open a new tab</a>
    </body>
</html>

Question4.Implement a basic form with a text input and a submit button.

Answer:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>
            anskey4
        </title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h2>Basic form  submission</h2>
        <form>
            <p> name
                <input type="name" id="mycheckbox"
                name="name">
            </p>
            <input type="submit">
        </form>
    </body>
</html>

